arts.ttl: Manchester City secure comeback victory in five-goal thriller against St Polten
arts.sum: Alanna Kennedy had given the visitors an early lead before the hosts hit back to lead in the second half.

arts.ttl: Bayern Munich, Man City win again in Women's Champions League groups
arts.sum: Harder pounced on a loose ball in the goalmouth after a corner in the 73rd minute in a near-copy of Linda Dallman’s volleyed shot in the 17th that opened the scoring. Man City won 3-2 at St. Pölten one week after a statement 2-0 victory over two-time defending champion Barcelona.

It was a busy first round of action several days ago as Bayern Munich crushed Arsenal 5-2, Manchester City recorded a shock 2-0 win over current holders Barcelona, and Chelsea scraped past Real Madrid 3-2 at Stamford Bridge. However, this week's Italian hosts had to beat Paris Saint-Germain in qualifying to reach the group stage of the competition, and they did so with an emphatic 5-2 aggregate win.

arts.ttl: St Polten Women vs Man City Women: Preview, predictions and lineups
arts.sum: Manchester City are back in Women's Champions League action on Wednesday evening as they take on St Polten in Vienna. Gareth Taylor's side recorded a statement victory on Matchday 1 of the group stage last week, comfortably beating back-to-back champions Barcelona 2-0 in Manchester.

arts.ttl: Man City boss Gareth Taylor responds to Chloe Kelly fall-out rumours
arts.sum: When asked about the rumours on Tuesday ahead of City’s Champions League clash against Austrian side St. Polten, Taylor described the story as a "non-event" and insisted Kelly is aligned with all they are doing at City and understands the intense competition for places at the top end of the pitch. Manchester City manager Gareth Taylor has described reports of a fall-out with England star Chloe Kelly as a "non-event".

arts.ttl: Parker earns England recall as James and Wubben-Moy return
arts.sum: Aston Villa defender Lucy Parker has earned a Lionesses recall as Lauren James and Lotte Wubben-Moy both return for international friendly fixtures against Germany and South Africa later this month.

arts.ttl: COMING UP: City train before St Polten UWCL trip
arts.sum: If you can’t watch it live, we’ll have a full recap of the open period of the session available shortly afterwards. Watch live as Gareth Taylor's team put the finishing touches in place before Wednesday's UEFA Women's Champions League trip to St Polten.
